sql:
SELECT name 
FROM datamarts 
WHERE owner_id = 1;

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_id, u.name
FROM users u
JOIN dispenses dp ON u.user_id = dp.dispensed_by;

external_knowledge:
Navigating through stormy seas of treatment - patients undergoing unsuccessful or complex treatments;
Weathered waves - types of treatments they have experienced;
Towering cliffs of surgery - metaphor for major, invasive treatments like surgeries;
Calm of successful responses - treatments that have led to positive outcomes or success.

- "guardians of knowledge" refers to users involved in the dispensing process;
- "cast their light on the matters of dispensation" metaphorically means they were involved in dispensing activities;
- "cold embrace of early winter" refers to the month of January in the year 2004;
- "designations in the vast cosmos of this data realm" indicates their roles within the data system.

sql:
SELECT AVG(strftime('%Y', 'now') - strftime('%Y', patients.date_of_birth)) AS average_age
FROM patients
INNER JOIN treatments ON patients.patient_id = treatments.patient_id;

SELECT d.name AS datamart_name, u.department AS department_name
FROM datamarts d
JOIN users u ON d.owner_id = u.user_id;

SELECT name
FROM datamarts
WHERE datamart_id = '0';

external_knowledge:
- Managing datamarts refers to users who own at least one datamart; 
- Detailed profiles include personal information (name, email), professional details (role, department), security (password hash), and recent interactions (creation, update, login timestamps);
- The status and permissions of these users are also considered part of their detailed profiles.

sql:
SELECT user_id, name, email, role, created_at, updated_at, status, password_hash, last_login_at, department, permissions
FROM users
WHERE user_id IN (
  SELECT owner_id FROM datamarts
);

SELECT name
FROM patients
WHERE patient_id > 2;

external_knowledge:
- 'active participants': users who have initiated queries and received responses;
- 'started the conversation': refers to users creating queries;
- 'received feedback': refers to having a valid response in the system (response_id is not null).

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_datamarts, status
FROM datamarts
GROUP BY status;
